n>\n\t\t\t\t\tPrice comparison from Backmarket\t\t\t\t\t\t</span>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div>\n\t\t\n\n\n<h2>SuperDrive</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>If you don’t know what Apple’s SuperDrive is, don’t be embarrassed. Because its days are definitely over: even the largest files (for personal use, at any rate) are now stored in the cloud. If you really want to save something to physical media, then USB sticks are a better choice than a DVD burner. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Apple discontinued the last Mac with a CD/DVD drive years ago: the MacBook Pro from 2012, which Apple sold until 2016. But the SuperDrive somehow made it to 2024 before <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/article/2419709/apple-stops-selling-its-superdrive-after-16-years-heres-where-to-still-buy-one.html\">finally expiring</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>AirPods Max with Lightning connector</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The AirPods Max went through a similar experience to the Magic accessories this fall, ditching Lightning in favour of the increasingly ubiquitous USB-C. Apple resisted as long as it could, but finally gave up the fight last year and equipped the iPhone 15 with USB-C. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The iPhone SE from 2022 is now the last product Apple sells that still has a Lightning port.</p>\n\n</div>","author":"","siteTitle":"Macworld","siteHash":"37e84dd5a21fa961d6d6630e269546024dbb7741b2e2fadbe74f47383c70dfbb","entryHash":"8c2356f791e3f07e2df2bf3cc7f1f1d820114f35bb343cfb1f7977c13e06760e","category":"Apple"}